President Donald J. Trump has declared a major disaster in the State of Delaware due to the impact of Tropical Storm Isaias from August 4 to August 7, 2020. This declaration allows for federal assistance to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas, specifically in Kent County. Federal funding will be available to state and eligible local governments, as well as certain private nonprofit organizations, for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures will also be supported on a cost-sharing basis statewide. Timothy S. Pheil has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected areas. Further designations may be made in the future based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.